// ===== Customer model v2 (organic acquisition + churn) =====
// Customers grow per in-game month from acquisition (reach × momentum + word-of-mouth
// referrals) minus churn (driven by weak engagement and founder stress), tapered by
// market saturation. Cards influence customers indirectly via reach/growth/engagement;
// explicit impact.customers values still apply as one-time shocks. Tunable knobs:
const CUSTOMER_MARKET_CAP   = 100000; // soft ceiling — acquisition tapers toward it
const CUSTOMER_ACQ_BASE     = 400;    // max organic new/mo from reach at full momentum
const CUSTOMER_REF_RATE     = 0.02;   // referrals: engaged existing customers bring others
const CUSTOMER_CHURN_BASE   = 0.10;   // up to 10%/mo lost when engagement = 0
const CUSTOMER_CHURN_STRESS = 0.05;   // extra monthly churn at max founder stress
// Pricing tradeoff: price above the "fair" baseline slows acquisition + adds churn;
// below it gives an acquisition bonus (cheap = faster growth).
const CUSTOMER_FAIR_PRICE     = 10;     // price/customer/mo with no growth penalty
const CUSTOMER_PRICE_ACQ_SENS = 40;    // $ above fair that fully suppresses acquisition
const CUSTOMER_PRICE_CHURN    = 0.002;  // extra monthly churn per $ above fair
const PRICE_STEP              = 5;      // bottom-nav stepper increment
// Metric decay: confidence/credibility/reach drift down each month without upkeep, so
// they can't just ratchet to 100 and stay there. Percentage decay — stronger near the
// top, gentle near 0. Reach fades fastest (attention), credibility slowest (reputation).
const REACH_DECAY       = 0.05; // 5%/mo
const GROWTH_DECAY      = 0.04; // 4%/mo — momentum fades without continued effort
const CONFIDENCE_DECAY  = 0.03; // 3%/mo
const CREDIBILITY_DECAY = 0.02; // 2%/mo

